# Always use the full name "CRC Public Relations"

In any user-visible copy across the My PR Partner site, the parent firm must always be referred to by its full name: **CRC Public Relations**.

## Never use

- `CRC` (bare — e.g. "senior CRC advisers", "CRC's clients", "facilitated by CRC", "the CRC consulting team")
- `CRC PR` (shortened)
- `CRCPR`, `crcpr` (except in domain URLs like `crcpr.com.au` where it is part of the URL string)

## Always use

- `CRC Public Relations` (full name, every time)
- `CRC Public Relations'` (possessive form, with trailing apostrophe — use `&apos;` in JSX)
- `CRC Public Relations consultant / adviser / team / clients` (full name as the modifier)

## Scope

Applies to every user-visible string: page copy, headings, CTAs, button labels, alt text, metadata titles and descriptions, JSON-LD, FAQ answers, testimonials, microcopy, toast messages, form placeholders — everywhere.

## Exceptions (allowed)

These are internal / non-rendered and do not need to be rewritten:

- JSX code comments, e.g. `{/* ── CRC DIRECT ENQUIRY BAND ── */}`
- Developer `// TODO:` notes referencing internal resources like "the CRC archive"
- Asset filenames such as `powered-by-crc-badge.svg` and `powered-by-crc-badge-light.svg`
- Domain URLs where "CRC" is part of the URL string (e.g. `crcpublicrelations.com.au`, `crcpr.com.au`)
- Variable/identifier names in code (e.g. `crcClients`, `CRC_URL`) — these are not rendered to users

## Rewriting guide

When editing or writing new copy, apply these substitutions:

- `senior CRC advisers` → `senior CRC Public Relations advisers`
- `CRC's clients` → `CRC Public Relations' clients` (JSX: `CRC Public Relations&apos; clients`)
- `CRC consulting team` → `CRC Public Relations consulting team`
- `facilitated by CRC` → `facilitated by CRC Public Relations`
- `tabletop day with CRC` → `tabletop day with CRC Public Relations`
- `the CRC archive` (internal dev note only) → leave as-is if it's a developer comment; rewrite if it's user-visible

## Verification

Before committing any copy changes, search for `\bCRC\b` (word-boundary) and confirm every match is followed by ` Public Relations` (or is one of the allowed exceptions above).
